KW  - Brokers
KW  - Market microstructure
KW  - Market quality
KW  - Market fragmentation
KW  - Make/take fees
AB  - I model investors who are only able to access equity markets through a broker. These brokers have an incentive to route based on the fees charged by exchanges, rather than on execution quality for their clients. This conflict of interest reduces investor utility, as they must pay higher commissions to have orders sent to exchanges with the best market quality. I show that regulators may be able to improve investor utility by allowing investors to self-direct order flow.
